CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, February 28, 1938, pg. unknown, reads: "Duke Ellington in center photo poses with a group of Pittsburgh admirers at the affair sponsored by the Synchronettes one of the newly formed Smoketown social clubs. (Pgh. photos by Charles 'Teenie' Harris)."
TitMainTitle: Duke Ellington holding glass with bandaged finger standing with group of men, including Alderman Harry Fitzgerald third from left, and women, posed in Loendi Club for Synchonettes Club party
